body:
Hi)

My project requires C++. I tried to add a C++ test file to the test project, but it didn't build:
```
CXX build_eh-lb523_hcpu\src\test_cpp_file.o
Error in calling command:g++
Exception: No such file or directory

Please check Toolchains PATH setting.

scons: *** [build_eh-lb523_hcpu\src\test_cpp_file.o] Error 2
CC build_eh-lb523_hcpu\sifli_sdk\rtos\kernel\src\clock.o
scons: building terminated because of errors.
```
I added the following line to SConstruct:
```
CXX = rtconfig.CXX, CXXFLAGS = rtconfig.CXXFLAGS,
```
The conclusion was as follows:
```
C:/proj/sifli_sdk/example/get-started/blink/rtt/src/test_cpp_file.cpp:1:1: error: unknown type name 'namespace'
namespace test_namespace {
^
C:/proj/sifli_sdk/example/get-started/blink/rtt/src/test_cpp_file.cpp:1:25: error: expected ';' after top level declarator
namespace test_namespace {
                        ^
                        ;
2 errors generated.
```
What do I need to do to get the files to start building? Here's the content of my test file:
```
namespace test_namespace {

class TestClass {
public:
        TestClass() = default;
};

};

```
